UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387893901109
AB  - Urban and rural areas are compared as appropriate locations for a free-trade zone within a developing country suffering from urban unemployment. If domestic capital is mobile between the two regions, then the rural area is shown to be preferable to the urban area, and sufficient conditions for this conclusion are presented. This conclusion may be reversed, however, if capital is sector-specific. The condition for this reversal is also discussed.
