AB  - In this note, we proceed to a macroeconomic analysis of speculative foodgrain stocks and of partial food price stabilization policies in a dual semi-industrialized economy of the type proposed by Rattsø (1989). We adopt a dynamic perspective which allows us to highlight the medium-run effects on industrial employment of their interaction with wage indexation in industry.
